  "notes": "Seoul standard. Three-way laryngeal contrast (lax/tense/aspirated). Extensive sandhi rules (nasalisation, lateralisation, tensification) apply at morpheme/word boundaries. Conjoining-jamo graphemes (U+1100 choseong, U+1161 jungseong, U+11A8 jongseong) carry the syllable-block decomposition: the engine canonically decomposes an unmapped Hangul syllable and reads these. Jongseong values encode coda neutralization (only k̚ n t̚ l m p̚ ŋ surface in coda; Sohn 1999 §6.2); cluster codas keep the pre-pause survivor. Cross-boundary phenomena (liaison/resyllabification 국어→[구거], nasalisation, tensification) are NOT yet modelled — transcriptions are per-syllable citation forms.",
